history.text: The Great Gatsby scored way lower on Rotten Tomatoes than I would have thought.
I agree.  With such a high star power cast in these roles I would think the critics would be more in love with the movie.
It is a very star studded cast. It's interesting that the introduction makes the connection to the novel, but the critical response seems to show that the novel was not really considered.
do you typically like romantic drama movies?
I enjoy them but they aren't my favorite.  Despite what most critics say about movies I like to judge for myself.  Do you go to movies based on what critics have said?
I'm with you on that. I typically don't pay attention to critics or ratings. I would rather see the movie for myself
Do you like movies where the actors are more well known?
It really depends on who the actor is. What about you?
Same.  But sometimes a big budget movie is more enjoyable to see than an indie film.
Apparently we have similar taste. This movie seemed to have a big budget
Do you also like period pieces?
I guess it depends on the time period it's set in. What about you?
Yeah I like them.  I also like how the 20
s  were represented here.
I have to disagree with you on that one. One of the critics said it was trashy and as much as that made me laugh, it's true.
That's funny.  But I did enjoy the introduction of the movie.  I like seeing the cast being introduced into their roles.
Yea, they set the scene well with Jay and his doctor in the beginning
I thought that Joel's take on Tom was very well portrayed.  He was quite intense.
Well tom is a very intense character, he's easy to hate. Edgertor did do a great job of that with his minimal screen time.

I didn't like the most critical part of the movie with the car accident. It seemed to be brushed ov
er too quickly
I wonder why they did that.  I think because Daisy is an unlikable character.
Ah finally someone who agrees with that! she's selfish!
Right!  She only seems to react emotionally.
She lets Jay take the fall (and get killed!) for her irrational response and then just leaves with her husband like she suddenly loves him? ugh shes the worst!
Even Nick, her cousin, is like "You people are the worst, I'm out of here"
Which was sad because he actually like Gatsby.
Right? It sends him to a mental institute..
because gatsby is the only likeable character.
He even names his own memoir after his friend
It's sad that gatsby died alone.

uid2response.feedback: I enjoyed this a lot. it was fun!
